{
  "texts": [
    "While many publicly available models (or online application interfaces) incorporate safety measures into their code (like detecting malicious text-based inputs) there are still cases where this is not sufficient for avoiding pornographic content generation (Robins-Early 2024).",
    "For researchers, steps should be taken to raise and act on concerns prior to releasing publicly available code, dataset or pre-trained models.",
    "F u r t h e r discussions: Riedl et al. (2010) and Elson and Riedl (2007).1",
